AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Data type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: List of the diferents types of data which are synchronized by Web POS
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: List of the diferents types of data which are synchronized by Web POS

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Your Company POS Login Image
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Default Your Company POS Login Image
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Image that will be shown in the POS login window. If it is not set, it will be used the default one set in "System Info" window in the field "Default Your Company Login Image"

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Error
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: It is the error message got when trying to import JSON data as an order.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a payment type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A descriptive identifier of a payment type that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: POS Terminal Type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A POS Terminal Type configures all generic settings that can be used by different POS Terminals. Each of these terminals defines the specific settings.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Type for Returns
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
Document type used for return orders generated in back end when a POS ticket is marked to be returned.
Document Types determine document sequence and processing rules.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Generate Invoice for Orders
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If checked, an invoice will be automatically generated for every order
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If checked, a sales invoice will be automatically generated for every sales order. This is actually a default value, and can always be changed from the Web POS once the order has been created, by clicking on the "Invoice" button.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: G/L Item for Cash drop/deposit
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In case of automated funds movement in cash up process, two new transactions for this movement are created both in current and destination financial accounts. These transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: JSON order data
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: JSON object sent from POS terminal
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: POS terminal serializes tickets in JSON format to be sent to back end.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Refund Provider
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: External payment provider who processes this kind of refund types.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: External payment provider who processes this kind of refund types.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: G/L Item for Writeoff
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In case the amount received when paying a ticket differs from what is expected, this G/L Item reflects this difference.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow not to Move
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Allows user to decide to keep all counted amount in current financial account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show stock screen
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is active a intermediate screen will appear in web pos when the product is added to the ticket. The screen will inform about the stock of the product
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If this flag is active a intermediate screen will appear in web pos when the product is added to the ticket. The screen will inform about the stock of the product

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Order Quotation No Prefix
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This is the prefix added to the document number for Quotations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Group orders in one Invoice
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In the cash up process, orders without invoice are grouped in one invoice per business partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Open drawer before closing ticket
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A flag which define if we want to open drawer before paying ticket
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A flag which define if we want to open drawer before paying ticket

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: G/L Item for Deposits
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When creating a deposit, two transactions are created: one in current financial account deposit the amount and another one in the origin financial account to take it out from there. Both of these transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Send Email
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this order is going to be sent by email.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A flag indicating whether this order is going to be sent by email. This option belongs to Web POS.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Scale URL
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: URL where the scale is in.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Time to incrementally refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Time to incrementally refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every incremental refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The incremental refresh is much lighter, less expensive and therefore can be completed quicker than a total refresh, but will not detect deletions of master data records.
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Payment Method
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Generic POS Terminal payment method which defines the generic settings for it, such as payment method (card, cash...) and cash up and cash management settings.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Email Status
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The Email Status indicates the status of sending email.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Email Status indicates the status of sending email. To change the status of sending email, complete the order in Web POS application.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: POS Classname
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: POS Classname represents a POS window or action can be assigned to roles.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Move Everything
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Includes an option in cash up process to move everything from current financial account, so cash up process would set it to 0.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: POS Terminal
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Web POS terminal

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Variable Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Allow to keep a variable amount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When checked, it will include in the cash up process the option to allow user to manually define the amount to be kept in current financial account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default tab for Web POS
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates which tab is selected in Web POS when the window is opened or a order is completed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates which tab is selected in Web POS when the window is opened or a order is completed

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Grouped Product
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Grouped Product

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: G/L Item for Withdrawals
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When creating a withdrawal, two transactions are created: one in current financial account to take out the amount and another one in the destination financial account to deposit it there. Both of these transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Cash differences
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This is the G/L Item used in Cash Up process in case there are differences between the expected and counted amount in this payment type. In this case a new transaction with this G/L Item and difference between expected and counted amounts will be created.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Clear error
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Once the error has been fixed and saved again, it is possible to remove it from the table by executing this process.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Deposits
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When deposits are allowed, it will be possible for POS users to deposit money in current financial account through Cash Management process.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Order Document No Prefix
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Each terminal needs to define a unique prefix to be added to the sales order document numbers generated from POS tickets making them unique.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: POS Product Category
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
Discount types marked as "POS Product Category" will be shown in POS as a Product Category, inside it all discounts of this type will be included.
The types flagged in this way, are required to implement a js method that will be invoked when an item inside the category is added. This method is in charge of implementing the logic to add the products.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Hardware URL
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: URL used by the printer and customer display.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Allow Withdrawals
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When withdrawals are allowed, it will be possible for POS users to drop money from current financial account from Cash Management process.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Payment Provider
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: External payment provider who processes this kind of payment types.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: External payment provider who processes this kind of payment types.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Time to fully refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_ELEMENT.PRINTNAME: Time to fully refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The total refresh can be a very expensive operation, and if done too much frequently it can tax the server, and decrease the performance of all POS terminals, so it is strongly recommended to set it to a high value (60 minutes, or greater if possible).
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Cash
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating is a cash method.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A payment type checked as flag shows when selected a panel with the coins and bank notes of the currency associated with this payment type.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default POS Role
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Role to be used by default in Web POS. This role must have access to Web POS form.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document type for Reconciliations
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When Cash Up process is executed from POS, a reconciliation including all transactions done in that terminal since last cash up is created. This is the document type used for that reconciliation.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Save again
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Try to process the order again
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: After fixing the data, the order can be processed again. Depending on the error, to fix the data can require to edit the JSON data to adjust it, or to properly set up configuration.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Automate Movement to Other Account
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
When this field is flagged, Cash Up process will transfer founds from the financial account in this payment method to the one defined in the close event. In case it is not flagged, Cash Up process will create a reconciliation but will keep all the amount in current financial account.
If checked, different options on how to do this movement can be defined by setting the rest of fields in this group.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Keep Fixed Amount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Allows to keep a fixed amount in the current financial account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Is scale
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Whether this product is sold by weight
